text: Ypsolopha longa is a moth of the family Ypsolophidae. It is known from Japan, Korea and Russia. The wingspan is 22–31 mm.Japanese Moths The larvae feed on Euonymus maackii and Euonymus sieboldianus. ==References== Category:Ypsolophidae Category:Moths of Asia Category:Moths of Russia
title: Ypsolopha longa
